This paper focuses on using human gaze patterns to enhance robot learning from demonstration, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper studies human-robot interaction during teaching, which is a subfield of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also uses computer vision techniques to analyze gaze patterns, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed algorithms for enhancing robot learning involve machine learning techniques, which fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
